net.cloud.server.entity.player

Class LoginHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.cloud.server.entity.player.LoginHandler

  • public class LoginHandler
extends Object
    Plain old static handler class. Encapsulates a good chunk of the code the server uses for the login process.

    • Method Detail

      • validationResponseFor

        public static LoginResponse validationResponseFor(Player player,
                                                  String username,
                                                  HashObj password)
        Determine what the appropriate response is for when someone is trying to login with the given username and password. Checks to make sure the account exists, the password matches, and that the account is not already logged in.
        Parameters:
        player - The player object that is going to be logged into
        username - The supposed username
        password - The supposed password
        Returns:
        A LoginResponse suitable to whatever conditions are or are not met

      • abortConnection

        public static void abortConnection(Player player)
        Aborts the connection the player is using. Consider this a forceful disconnect, there is not attempt to save the player data. Useful for when the login process fails.
        Parameters:
        player - The player to terminate

      • doLogout

        public static void doLogout(Player player)
        Do the log out process for a player. This will actually run through the actions needed to log a player out of the game
        Parameters:
        player - The player that is about to leave the game

      • resumeLogout

        private static void resumeLogout(Player player)
        Pick up where doLogout left off, wrapping up the server side end of logging out
        Parameters:
        player - The player that was just told to log out

      • handleDisconnect

        public static void handleDisconnect(Player player)
        Should be called when the player disconnects from the game. It's okay if they're gracefully logging out, this will do nothing, then. Takes care of what should happen if the player abruptly disconnects from the game.
        Parameters:
        player - The player that is no longer connected to the server

      • doReconnectFailed

        public static void doReconnectFailed(Player player)
        Called when the timer runs up on the task to reconnect. If the player has reconnected, this will simply return. If they have not, then the player is considered to have failed reconnect, and action is taken for that.
        Parameters:
        player - The player that disconnected

      • reconnectingTimeoutTask

        public static void reconnectingTimeoutTask(Player player)
        Called when the time is up between the reconnecting and logged in transition. If the player has moved out of the reconnecting state, this will simply return. Otherwise, the player is considered to have a failed reconnect, and action is taken for that.
        Parameters:
        player - The player that tried to reconnect
